<!DOCTYPE HTML><html><head>	<meta charset="UTF-8" />	<title>Linux 101</title>	<link href="../../styles/prism.css" rel="stylesheet" />	<link href="../../styles/style.css" rel="stylesheet" />	<script src="../../scripts/jquery-2.1.1.min.js"></script>	<script src="../../scripts/lesson.js"></script></head><body>	<h1>Linux 101</h1>	<h3>What is Linux?</h3>	<p>To make it simple, Linux is an operating system just like Mac OS X or Windows. Linux has many variations called distros. There are over 600 distributions to choose from.</p>	<h3>What are Linux's features?</h3>	<ul>		<li>Open Source</li>		<li>Free (most distros)</li>		<li>Excellent stability</li>		<li>Endless customization</li>		<li>Small size</li>		<li>Low system requirements</li>	</ul>	<h3>Ubuntu</h3>	<p>To have an experience that is as easy as Mac OS X choose Ubuntu</p>	<figure>		<img src="ubuntu.png" />		<figcaption>Fig. 1 The Ubuntu interface</figcaption>	</figure>	<p>Features</p>	<ul>		<li>Developed by Canonical</li>		<li>Stable</li>		<li>Easy</li>		<li>The most popular distro</li>		<li>Going mobile</li>		<li>Easy UI</li>	</ul>	<h3>Manjaro</h3>	<p>To have an experience that is straight out of the box ready choose Manjaro</p>	<figure>		<img src="manjaro.png" />		<figcaption>Fig. 2 The Manjaro interface</figcaption>	</figure>	<p>Features</p>	<ul>		<li>Based on Arch</li>		<li>Suite of applications</li>		<li>Easy</li>		<li>Fast</li>		<li>Powerful</li>	</ul>	<h3>Gentoo</h3>	<p>To have an experience that is as hard choose Gentoo</p>	<figure>		<img src="gentoo.png" width="1000" />		<figcaption>Fig. 1 The Gentoo interface</figcaption>	</figure>	<p>Features</p>	<ul>		<li>Super customizable</li>		<li>Barebones minimum</li>		<li>Hard</li>		<li>Advanced</li>		<li>Fast</li>	</ul>	<h3>How do I install Linux?</h3>	<ul>		<li>Virtually (Virtual Machines)</li>		<li>Live CD/DVD</li>		<li>Live USB</li>	</ul>	<h3>VM</h3>	<p>A virtual machine allows you to run an OS inside your own operating system</p>	<ul>		<li>1. Download .iso or insert CD/DVD</li>		<li>2. Run VM wizard</li>		<li>3. Enter Options and continue</li>		<li>4. Rest is done for you!</li>	</ul>	<h3>Live CD/DVD</h3>	<p>CAREFULL: Partitioning your drive might delete data on your drive</p>	<ul>		<li>1. Download .iso</li>		<li>2. Mount onto DVD/CD</li>		<li>3. Place in computer</li>		<li>4. Boot from CD/DVD</li>		<li>4. Install onto HDD</li>	</ul>	<h3>Live USB</h3>	<p>CAREFULL: Partitioning your drive might delete data on your drive</p>	<ul>		<li>1. Download .iso</li>		<li>2. Mount onto USB</li>		<li>3. Place in computer</li>		<li>4. Boot from USB</li>		<li>4. Install onto HDD</li>	</ul>	<script src="../../scripts/prism.js"></script>	<?php include('../../footer.php')?></body></html>